{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01Hz6mWPLXcXqBn3BPo8YX2D","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_017AsRyueb4GDCHPKv6Na485","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/cmd/cloche/help.go","limit":200},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1917,"cache_read_input_tokens":55395,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1917,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01YBDNVBTQUf847DxND28odt","session_id":"955b2dd5-cc52-456b-afc0-0035f6eae0d8","uuid":"0981304a-4dea-4300-8ce7-ff87af303fb9"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017AsRyueb4GDCHPKv6Na485","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package main\n     2→\n     3→import (\n     4→\t\"fmt\"\n     5→\t\"os\"\n     6→)\n     7→\n     8→// subcommandHelp maps each subcommand to its detailed help text.\n     9→// Help text is formatted for LLM consumption: structured, explicit, with examples.\n    10→var subcommandHelp = map[string]string{\n    11→\t\"init\": `cloche init — Initialize a Cloche project\n    12→\n    13→Creates the .cloche/ directory with a workflow definition, Dockerfile,\n    14→prompt templates, and configuration files.\n    15→\n    16→Usage:\n    17→  cloche init [--workflow <name>] [--base-image <image>]\n    18→\n    19→Flags:\n    20→  --workflow <name>       Name for the workflow file (default: \"develop\")\n    21→  --base-image <image>    Base Docker image for the Dockerfile (default: \"cloche-base:latest\")\n    22→\n    23→What it creates:\n    24→  .cloche/<name>.cloche           Workflow definition\n    25→  .cloche/host.cloche             Host orchestration workflow\n    26→  .cloche/Dockerfile              Container image definition\n    27→  .cloche/config.toml             Project configuration\n    28→  .cloche/prompts/implement.md    Prompt for the implement step\n    29→  .cloche/prompts/fix.md          Prompt for the fix step\n    30→  .cloche/prompts/update-docs.md  Prompt for the update-docs step\n    31→  .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh  Prompt generation script\n    32→  .cloche/version                 Schema version marker\n    33→\n    34→Existing files are never overwritten. Run this command again safely to add\n    35→missing files without losing customizations.\n    36→\n    37→Examples:\n    38→  cloche init\n    39→  cloche init --workflow build --base-image python:3.12\n    40→`,\n    41→\n    42→\t\"health\": `cloche health — Show project health summary\n    43→\n    44→Queries the daemon's HTTP API for a summary of all registered projects\n    45→and their pass/fail test counts.\n    46→\n    47→Usage:\n    48→  cloche health\n    49→\n    50→Environment:\n    51→  CLOCHE_HTTP    Daemon HTTP address (e.g. \"localhost:8080\"). Required.\n    52→\n    53→Examples:\n    54→  export CLOCHE_HTTP=localhost:8080\n    55→  cloche health\n    56→`,\n    57→\n    58→\t\"run\": `cloche run — Launch a workflow run\n    59→\n    60→Starts a new container workflow run. The daemon builds/pulls the container\n    61→image, copies the project into it, and executes the workflow steps.\n    62→\n    63→Usage:\n    64→  cloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]\n    65→  cloche run <name>              (shorthand: bare positional workflow name)\n    66→\n    67→Flags:\n    68→  --workflow <name>    Name of the workflow to run (required). Must match a\n    69→                       .cloche/<name>.cloche file in the project.\n    70→  --prompt \"...\"       Prompt text passed to agent steps. Also available as\n    71→  -p \"...\"             the short form.\n    72→  --title \"...\"        Human-readable title for the run (shown in status/list).\n    73→  --keep-container     Do not remove the container after the run completes.\n    74→                       Useful for debugging.\n    75→\n    76→The command prints the run ID on success. Use that ID with status, logs,\n    77→poll, and stop.\n    78→\n    79→Examples:\n    80→  cloche run --workflow develop --prompt \"Add a /health endpoint\"\n    81→  cloche run develop -p \"Fix the broken CSV parser\" --title \"CSV fix\"\n    82→  cloche run --workflow build --keep-container\n    83→`,\n    84→\n    85→\t\"status\": `cloche status — Check run status\n    86→\n    87→Shows the current state of a workflow run including its type, active step,\n    88→and the result of each completed step.\n    89→\n    90→Usage:\n    91→  cloche status <run-id>\n    92→\n    93→Arguments:\n    94→  <run-id>    The run identifier returned by \"cloche run\".\n    95→\n    96→Output fields:\n    97→  Run         Run identifier\n    98→  Title       Human-readable title (if set)\n    99→  Workflow    Workflow name\n   100→  Type        \"host\" or \"container\"\n   101→  State       Current state (e.g. running, succeeded, failed, cancelled)\n   102→  Container   Truncated container ID (container runs only)\n   103→  Error       Error message (if failed)\n   104→  Active      Name of the currently executing step\n   105→  Steps       List of completed steps with results and timestamps\n   106→\n   107→Examples:\n   108→  cloche status abc123\n   109→`,\n   110→\n   111→\t\"logs\": `cloche logs — Show logs for a run\n   112→\n   113→Streams or displays log output for a workflow run. Supports filtering by\n   114→step name and log type, limiting output, and following live output.\n   115→\n   116→Usage:\n   117→  cloche logs <run-id> [-s <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [-f] [-l <n>]\n   118→\n   119→Arguments:\n   120→  <run-id>    The run identifier.\n   121→\n   122→Flags:\n   123→  --step, -s <name>              Show logs only for the named step.\n   124→  --type <full|script|llm>       Filter by log type:\n   125→                                   full    — complete unfiltered output\n   126→                                   script  — script/command output only\n   127→                                   llm     — LLM interaction logs only\n   128→  --follow, -f                   Stream logs in real time (blocks until the\n   129→                                 run completes or is stopped).\n   130→  --limit, -l <n>                Display only the last n lines of output.\n   131→\n   132→Flags are combinable: cloche logs run-id -s implement -l 20 -f\n   133→\n   134→Examples:\n   135→  cloche logs abc123\n   136→  cloche logs abc123 -s implement\n   137→  cloche logs abc123 -s implement -l 20\n   138→  cloche logs abc123 -f\n   139→  cloche logs abc123 -s test --type script\n   140→  cloche logs abc123 -s implement -l 20 -f\n   141→`,\n   142→\n   143→\t\"poll\": `cloche poll — Wait for runs to finish\n   144→\n   145→Polls the daemon every 2 seconds until all runs reach a terminal state\n   146→(succeeded, failed, or cancelled).\n   147→\n   148→With a single run ID, prints step-level progress (same as before).\n   149→With multiple run IDs, displays a compact status summary.\n   150→\n   151→Usage:\n   152→  cloche poll <run-id> [run-id...]\n   153→\n   154→Arguments:\n   155→  <run-id>    One or more run identifiers.\n   156→\n   157→Exit codes:\n   158→  0    All runs succeeded.\n   159→  1    Any run failed, was cancelled, or the container died.\n   160→\n   161→Examples:\n   162→  cloche poll abc123\n   163→  cloche poll abc123 def456 ghi789\n   164→  cloche run develop -p \"Fix bug\" && cloche poll \"$(cloche run develop -p 'Fix bug')\"\n   165→`,\n   166→\n   167→\t\"list\": `cloche list — List workflow runs\n   168→\n   169→Shows all runs for the current project, or all runs across all projects\n   170→with --all. Results can be filtered by state, project, issue, or limited\n   171→to a fixed number.\n   172→\n   173→Usage:\n   174→  cloche list [flags]\n   175→\n   176→Flags:\n   177→  --all              Show runs from all projects (default: current project only).\n   178→  --project, -p DIR  Filter by project directory.\n   179→  --state, -s STATE  Filter by run state (pending, running, succeeded, failed, cancelled).\n   180→  --limit, -n NUM    Limit the number of results returned.\n   181→  --issue, -i ID     Filter by issue/task ID.\n   182→\n   183→Output columns: run ID, workflow name, state, type (host/container),\n   184→title, container ID, and error message (if any).\n   185→\n   186→Examples:\n   187→  cloche list\n   188→  cloche list --all\n   189→  cloche list --state running\n   190→  cloche list --limit 10\n   191→  cloche list --all --state failed --limit 5\n   192→  cloche list --issue TASK-123\n   193→  cloche list -p /home/user/project -s succeeded -n 20\n   194→`,\n   195→\n   196→\t\"stop\": `cloche stop — Stop a running workflow\n   197→\n   198→Sends a stop signal to a running workflow. The container is terminated\n   199→and the run state transitions to \"cancelled\".\n   200→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01YBDNVBTQUf847DxND28odt","session_id":"955b2dd5-cc52-456b-afc0-0035f6eae0d8","uuid":"2e19c582-d51a-487e-9690-a142a29485b2"}
