{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01LS68VYn1hBjSWo2rxhBSuA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01TmuTcaww3QNnPohQP9LBdM","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/cmd/cloche/help.go","offset":200,"limit":300},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2582,"cache_read_input_tokens":57312,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2582,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01YBDNVBTQUf847DxND28odt","session_id":"955b2dd5-cc52-456b-afc0-0035f6eae0d8","uuid":"7fb0f292-ccd8-44b8-987a-e454ded193a7"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TmuTcaww3QNnPohQP9LBdM","type":"tool_result","content":"   200→\n   201→Usage:\n   202→  cloche stop <run-id>\n   203→\n   204→Arguments:\n   205→  <run-id>    The run identifier.\n   206→\n   207→Examples:\n   208→  cloche stop abc123\n   209→`,\n   210→\n   211→\t\"delete\": `cloche delete — Delete a retained container\n   212→\n   213→Removes a container that was kept after a run (via --keep-container).\n   214→Accepts either a container ID or a run ID.\n   215→\n   216→Usage:\n   217→  cloche delete <container-or-run-id>\n   218→\n   219→Arguments:\n   220→  <container-or-run-id>    Container ID or run ID to delete.\n   221→\n   222→Examples:\n   223→  cloche delete abc123\n   224→`,\n   225→\n   226→\t\"tasks\": `cloche tasks — Show task pipeline and assignment state\n   227→\n   228→Queries the daemon's HTTP API for the current task list, showing which\n   229→tasks are open, assigned, or completed.\n   230→\n   231→Usage:\n   232→  cloche tasks [--project <dir>]\n   233→\n   234→Flags:\n   235→  --project <dir>    Project directory name to query (default: current\n   236→                     directory basename).\n   237→\n   238→Environment:\n   239→  CLOCHE_HTTP    Daemon HTTP address (default: \"localhost:8080\").\n   240→\n   241→Output columns: ID, STATUS, ASSIGNED, RUN, TITLE\n   242→\n   243→Examples:\n   244→  cloche tasks\n   245→  cloche tasks --project my-app\n   246→`,\n   247→\n   248→\t\"loop\": `cloche loop — Manage the orchestration loop\n   249→\n   250→Starts, stops, or resumes the daemon's orchestration loop, which\n   251→automatically picks up and runs tasks from the task pipeline.\n   252→\n   253→Usage:\n   254→  cloche loop [--max <n>]     Start the orchestration loop\n   255→  cloche loop stop            Stop the orchestration loop\n   256→  cloche loop resume          Resume a halted loop (clear error state)\n   257→\n   258→Flags:\n   259→  --max <n>    Maximum number of concurrent runs (default: value from\n   260→               .cloche/config.toml).\n   261→\n   262→When stop_on_error is enabled in .cloche/config.toml, an unrecovered\n   263→error will halt the loop. Use \"cloche loop resume\" to clear the error\n   264→and resume picking up new work.\n   265→\n   266→Examples:\n   267→  cloche loop\n   268→  cloche loop --max 3\n   269→  cloche loop stop\n   270→  cloche loop resume\n   271→`,\n   272→\n   273→\t\"get\": `cloche get — Get a value from the run context store\n   274→\n   275→Reads a key from the run's context.json file. Intended for use inside\n   276→workflow scripts and steps.\n   277→\n   278→Usage:\n   279→  cloche get <key>\n   280→\n   281→Arguments:\n   282→  <key>    The context key to read.\n   283→\n   284→Environment:\n   285→  CLOCHE_RUN_ID        Run identifier (required).\n   286→  CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR   Project directory (default: current directory).\n   287→\n   288→Exit codes:\n   289→  0    Key exists; value printed to stdout.\n   290→  1    Key not found or error.\n   291→\n   292→Examples:\n   293→  cloche get branch\n   294→  cloche get task_id\n   295→`,\n   296→\n   297→\t\"set\": `cloche set — Set a value in the run context store\n   298→\n   299→Writes a key-value pair to the run's context.json file. Use \"-\" as the\n   300→value to read from stdin (useful for multi-line content).\n   301→\n   302→Usage:\n   303→  cloche set <key> <value>\n   304→  cloche set <key> -          (read value from stdin)\n   305→\n   306→Arguments:\n   307→  <key>      The context key to write.\n   308→  <value>    The value to store, or \"-\" to read from stdin.\n   309→\n   310→Environment:\n   311→  CLOCHE_RUN_ID        Run identifier (required).\n   312→  CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR   Project directory (default: current directory).\n   313→\n   314→Examples:\n   315→  cloche set branch feature-auth\n   316→  echo \"multi-line content\" | cloche set notes -\n   317→`,\n   318→\n   319→\t\"workflow\": `cloche workflow — View workflow definitions\n   320→\n   321→Lists all workflows in the project or renders a specific workflow as an\n   322→ASCII-art graph showing steps, wiring, and result paths.\n   323→\n   324→Usage:\n   325→  cloche workflow [--project <dir>]          List all workflows\n   326→  cloche workflow <name> [--project <dir>]   Show workflow graph\n   327→\n   328→Arguments:\n   329→  <name>    Name of the workflow to render as a graph.\n   330→\n   331→Flags:\n   332→  --project <dir>, -p <dir>    Project directory (default: current directory).\n   333→\n   334→When listing, workflows are grouped by type (container or host). When\n   335→showing a specific workflow, the output is a graph with step boxes and\n   336→colored wires: green for success, red for fail/failed, and\n   337→blue/yellow/orange/magenta for other result paths. Wires to the same\n   338→destination are merged for readability.\n   339→\n   340→Examples:\n   341→  cloche workflow\n   342→  cloche workflow develop\n   343→  cloche workflow main -p /path/to/project\n   344→  cloche workflow --project ../other-project\n   345→`,\n   346→\n   347→\t\"project\": `cloche project — Show project info and config\n   348→\n   349→Displays project-level information including config settings, orchestrator\n   350→loop state, concurrency, active runs, and known workflows.\n   351→\n   352→By default, looks up the project by the current working directory. Use\n   353→--name to look up a project by its label instead.\n   354→\n   355→Usage:\n   356→  cloche project [--name <label>]\n   357→\n   358→Flags:\n   359→  --name <label>    Look up project by label (e.g. \"cloche\") instead of\n   360→                    the current directory.\n   361→\n   362→Output includes:\n   363→  Config            active, concurrency, stagger, dedup, stop_on_error,\n   364→                    evolution settings\n   365→  Loop              Orchestration loop state (running, stopped, or halted)\n   366→  Active runs       Currently pending or running workflow runs\n   367→  Workflows         Known container and host workflow names\n   368→\n   369→Environment:\n   370→  CLOCHE_ADDR    Daemon gRPC address (default: unix:///tmp/cloche.sock)\n   371→\n   372→Examples:\n   373→  cloche project\n   374→  cloche project --name cloche\n   375→  cloche project --name my-app\n   376→`,\n   377→\n   378→\t\"shutdown\": `cloche shutdown — Shut down the daemon\n   379→\n   380→Sends a shutdown signal to the Cloche daemon. Refuses to shut down if\n   381→there are active runs unless --force is specified.\n   382→\n   383→Usage:\n   384→  cloche shutdown [--force|-f]\n   385→\n   386→Flags:\n   387→  -f, --force   Shut down even if runs are still active.\n   388→\n   389→Examples:\n   390→  cloche shutdown\n   391→  cloche shutdown --force\n   392→`,\n   393→}\n   394→\n   395→// printHelp prints the top-level help or subcommand-specific help.\n   396→// Returns true if help was printed (caller should exit).\n   397→func printHelp(args []string) bool {\n   398→\tif len(args) == 0 {\n   399→\t\tprintTopLevelHelp()\n   400→\t\treturn true\n   401→\t}\n   402→\n   403→\t// \"cloche help <subcommand>\"\n   404→\tcmd := args[0]\n   405→\tif text, ok := subcommandHelp[cmd]; ok {\n   406→\t\tfmt.Fprint(os.Stderr, text)\n   407→\t\treturn true\n   408→\t}\n   409→\n   410→\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"unknown command: %s\\n\\n\", cmd)\n   411→\tprintTopLevelHelp()\n   412→\treturn true\n   413→}\n   414→\n   415→// hasHelpFlag returns true if the args contain --help or -h.\n   416→func hasHelpFlag(args []string) bool {\n   417→\tfor _, arg := range args {\n   418→\t\tif arg == \"--help\" || arg == \"-h\" {\n   419→\t\t\treturn true\n   420→\t\t}\n   421→\t}\n   422→\treturn false\n   423→}\n   424→\n   425→// printSubcommandHelp prints help for a subcommand and exits.\n   426→func printSubcommandHelp(cmd string) {\n   427→\tif text, ok := subcommandHelp[cmd]; ok {\n   428→\t\tfmt.Fprint(os.Stderr, text)\n   429→\t} else {\n   430→\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"no help available for %q\\n\", cmd)\n   431→\t}\n   432→}\n   433→\n   434→func printTopLevelHelp() {\n   435→\tfmt.Fprint(os.Stderr, `cloche — Grow-code high quality applications\n   436→\n   437→Cloche provides containerized environments for coding agents, a workflow DSL\n   438→for linking agentic and script-driven tasks, and validated code pipelines.\n   439→\n   440→Usage:\n   441→  cloche <command> [args]\n   442→  cloche help <command>       Show detailed help for a command\n   443→  cloche <command> --help     Same as above\n   444→\n   445→Project Setup:\n   446→  init       Initialize a Cloche project (.cloche/ directory and templates)\n   447→  health     Show project health summary (pass/fail counts)\n   448→  project    Show project info, config, loop state, and workflows\n   449→\n   450→Workflow Info:\n   451→  workflow   List workflows or show a workflow as an ASCII-art graph\n   452→\n   453→Workflow Runs:\n   454→  run        Launch a workflow run in a container\n   455→  status     Check run status (state, steps, errors)\n   456→  logs       Show or stream logs for a run\n   457→  poll       Wait for one or more runs to finish (blocks until terminal)\n   458→  list       List runs for current project (or all projects)\n   459→  stop       Stop a running workflow\n   460→  delete     Delete a retained container\n   461→\n   462→Orchestration:\n   463→  tasks      Show task pipeline and assignment state\n   464→  loop       Start or stop the orchestration loop\n   465→\n   466→Context Store (for use inside workflow steps):\n   467→  get        Get a value from the run context store\n   468→  set        Set a value in the run context store\n   469→\n   470→Daemon:\n   471→  shutdown   Shut down the Cloche daemon\n   472→\n   473→Environment Variables:\n   474→  CLOCHE_ADDR          Daemon gRPC address (default: unix:///tmp/cloche.sock)\n   475→  CLOCHE_HTTP          Daemon HTTP address (for health/tasks commands)\n   476→  CLOCHE_RUN_ID        Run ID for get/set commands (set automatically in steps)\n   477→  CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR   Project directory override for get/set commands\n   478→\n   479→Examples:\n   480→  cloche init\n   481→  cloche run --workflow develop --prompt \"Add user authentication\"\n   482→  cloche status abc123\n   483→  cloche logs abc123 --follow\n   484→  cloche list\n   485→  cloche loop --max 2\n   486→`)\n   487→}\n   488→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01YBDNVBTQUf847DxND28odt","session_id":"955b2dd5-cc52-456b-afc0-0035f6eae0d8","uuid":"dc69f7ea-7a91-4643-b023-c44a03a01c19"}
